# Ollama Modelfile for Gemma 3 with citation awareness
#
# The middleware sends its own detailed system prompt on each /api/generate
# call (see core/extractor.SYSTEM_PROMPT), which takes precedence over the
# SYSTEM block below. This Modelfile mainly exists to:
#   - pin deterministic parameters (temperature 0.0, num_ctx 8192)
#   - give the model a baseline priming for citation-aware conversation
#
# IMPORTANT: The FROM line must match OLLAMA_MODEL in config.py.
#
# Build: ollama create gemma3-1b-cite -f Modelfile

FROM gemma3:1b

SYSTEM """You are a helpful assistant with strong academic citation awareness.
When you produce an answer, you will also be asked to list every source you
relied on. After your natural-language answer, output the literal marker
---REFERENCES--- on its own line, followed by a JSON array of the sources.
Each JSON item must include: title, authors, date, source_type, citation_style,
publisher, doi, url, raw_fragment, confidence. Do not invent sources."""

PARAMETER temperature 0.0
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
PARAMETER num_predict 4096
